'''ᱩᱛᱠᱚᱲ ᱥᱚᱢᱢᱤᱲᱚᱱᱤ''' ({{lang-or|[[:or:ଉତ୍କଳ ସମ୍ମିଳନୀ|'''ଉତ୍କଳ ସମ୍ମିଳନୀ''']]}}) ᱫᱚ ᱢᱤᱫ [[ᱵᱷᱟᱨᱚᱛ]]ᱤᱭᱚ ᱥᱟᱶᱛᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱞᱟᱠᱪᱟᱨ ᱜᱟᱶᱛᱟ ᱠᱟᱱᱟ ᱾ [[ᱳᱰᱤᱥᱟ]] ᱨᱮ ᱑᱙᱐᱓ ᱨᱮ [[ᱢᱚᱫᱷᱩᱥᱩᱫᱚᱱ ᱫᱟᱥ]] ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱜᱟᱶᱛᱟ ᱫᱚᱭ ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱣ ᱞᱮᱭᱟ ᱾ <ref name="Hindu Times">{{cite web | title=Central Nod to Rename Orissa Welcome | publisher=Hindustan Times (New Delhi) | date=24 October 2009 | author=Staff Reporter}}</ref>

==ᱱᱟᱜᱟᱢ==
ᱩᱛᱠᱚᱲ ᱥᱚᱢᱤᱤᱲᱚᱱᱤ ᱫᱚ [[ᱢᱚᱫᱷᱩᱥᱩᱫᱚᱱ ᱫᱟᱥ]] ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱣ ᱞᱮᱭᱟ ᱾ <ref name="Odisha Gov">{{cite web | url=http://www.odisha.gov.in/portal/LIWPL/event_archive/Events_Archives/148Death_Annivearsary_Madhusudan_Das.pdf | title=Death Anniversary of Utkal Gaurab Madhusudan Das | publisher=Odisha Government | accessdate=17 September 2013 | author=Unknown author}}</ref> ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱨᱮᱱᱟᱝ ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱜᱟᱞᱚᱪ ᱫᱚ ᱑᱙᱐᱓ ᱨᱮ ᱦᱩᱭ ᱞᱮᱱᱟ ᱾ ᱩᱱ ᱚᱠᱛᱚ ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱨᱤᱱ ᱖᱒ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱯᱟᱨᱢᱟᱱᱮᱱᱴ ᱢᱮᱢᱵᱚᱨ ᱠᱚ ᱛᱟᱦᱮᱸ ᱠᱟᱱᱟ ᱾ <ref name="Shakti Malik">{{cite book|title=Makers of Modern Orissa|publisher=|year=1996|isbn=|location=|pages=48|quote=|via=|author1=Samal, Joy K.|author2=Nayak, Pradip Kumar|lastauthoramp=yes}}</ref> ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱜᱟᱶᱛᱟ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱡᱚᱥ ᱫᱚ ᱳᱰᱤᱥᱟ ᱯᱚᱱᱚᱛ ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱣ ᱠᱚ ᱴᱷᱟ.ᱣᱠᱟ. ᱞᱮᱭᱟ ᱾ <ref>{{cite book | title=Indian Political Thought | publisher=PHI Learning Private Ltd | author=Padhy, K.S. | year=2011 | pages=287}}</ref>
 
᱑᱙᱒᱐ ᱨᱮ ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱡᱮᱠᱷᱟ [[ᱪᱚᱠᱨᱚᱫᱷᱚᱨᱯᱩᱨ]] ᱨᱮ ᱜᱟᱞᱚᱪ ᱦᱩᱭ ᱥᱟ.ᱵᱤᱛ ᱞᱮᱱᱟ ᱾ ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱜᱟᱞᱚᱪ ᱨᱮ ᱴᱷᱟ.ᱣᱠᱟ. ᱞᱮᱱᱟ ᱡᱮ ᱵᱷᱟᱨᱚᱛ ᱨᱮ [[ᱤᱱᱰᱤᱭᱟᱱ ᱱᱮᱥᱱᱟᱞ ᱠᱚᱝᱜᱽᱨᱮᱥ]] ᱦᱮᱯᱨᱟᱣ ᱛᱮ ᱪᱟ.ᱞᱩ ᱟᱠᱟᱱ ᱚᱥᱚᱦᱚᱡᱳᱜᱽ ᱟᱱᱫᱳᱲᱚᱱ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱚ ᱥᱮᱞᱮᱫᱚᱜ-ᱟ ᱾ <ref>{{cite book | title=My Life, My work | publisher=Allied Publishers Private | author=Mahapatra, Jarihar | year=2011 | pages=220}}</ref> It elected a new president, Basanta Kumar Panigrahi, in 2002.<ref name="Orissa Matters">{{cite web | url=http://orissamatters.com/2002/11/30/new-leader-of-utkal-sammilani/ | title=New Leader of Utkal Sammilani | publisher=Orrisa Matters | date=30 November 2002 | accessdate=17 September 2013 | author=Pattanayak, Subhas Chandra}}</ref>
 
᱒᱐᱑᱐ ᱨᱮ ᱩᱛᱠᱚᱲ ᱥᱚᱢᱢᱤᱲᱚᱱᱤ ᱯᱟᱦᱴᱟ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱵᱷᱟᱨᱚᱛ ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱤᱝᱨᱮᱡᱽ ᱥᱚᱨᱠᱟᱨ ᱠᱚ ᱱᱮᱦᱚᱨ ᱠᱮᱫᱮᱭ ᱡᱮ, ᱳᱰᱤᱭᱟ ᱫᱚ "classical language status" ᱜᱽᱨᱟᱸᱴ ᱧᱟᱢ ᱢᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱟᱨ ᱚᱱᱟ ᱚᱢᱥᱟᱨ ᱳᱰᱤᱥᱟ ᱯᱚᱱᱚᱛ ᱠᱚ ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱣ ᱢᱟ ᱾ <ref name="The Hindu">{{cite news | title=Utkal Sammilani's demand | newspaper=The Hindu | date=7 December 2010 | author=Staff Reporter}}</ref> Utkal Sammilani was a key player in the transformation of the state of [[Orissa, India|Orissa]] to its modern-day status as Odisha and it opposed [[Andhra Pradesh]]’s Polavaram project in 2010.<ref name="The Hindu 2">{{cite news | title=Protest Against | newspaper=The Hindu | date=15 September 2010 }}</ref>

